               <msContents class="#CM">
                  <summary><p>A catalogue of the Tamil manuscripts in the now BnF by Léon Feer, according to the title on the spine.</p>
<p>The codex contains:
<list rend="numbered">
  <item>a list of 63 manuscripts (Tamil, Sanskrit, Telugu, Kannada) sent by the Jesuits of Pondicherry (U1)</item>
  <item>an alphabetical list of the Tamil works in the BnF manuscripts: title in Tamil transcription, title in Roman transliteration, translation in French (in red ink), and shelfmark (U2)</item>
  </list>
</p>
<p>Composite manuscript described as a multi-text manuscript for the sake of convenience.</p>
<p>Description based on the digital images available on Gallica.</p></summary>
                  
